The defendant Frederick Eugene Walker was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Repeated Sexual Assault of Same Child (At Least 3 Violations of 1st or 2nd Degree Sexual Assault), a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.025(1)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Frederick Eugene Walker in court with attorney Robert E Haney.  Defendant Frederick Eugene Walker in custody.  Joshua Miles Mathy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Sentencing proceeded.  Victim notification was made.  Presentence Investigation reviewed.  Additions and corrections were made.  Statements by state, defense.  The defendant chooses not to make a statement but later in the hearing became argumentative on the record.
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 27 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, credit for 417 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 17 YEARS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 10 YEARS with the following conditions:
-The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
Restitution is set at ZERO.
-Pay all costs, assessments and victim/witness surcharges, DNA surcharge.
-Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
-No contact with victim, TCB, dob 5-23-1998, or her mother, Nakia S.
-No contact with children under the age of 17 years.
-Defendant to register as sex offender.
The defendant is advised as a convicted felon he may not carry or possess any firearms/body armor.
The court advises the defendant that voting privileges are suspended during the length of this sentence.
The defendant is given a written explanation of the determinate sentence, and advised of his appeal rights by defense counsel.
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.   
The defendant is not eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is remanded and is report to Dodge.

Defendant Frederick Eugene Walker in court with attorney Robert E Haney.  Defendant Frederick Eugene Walker in custody.  Joshua Miles Mathy appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Trial resumed. Side bar place on the record. Jury in the box at 9:00am.  Sworn for the state:  Det. Carmen Rodgers (MPD); Exhibit 5 received.  State rests subject to rebuttal.  Jury out of box 9:40 am.  Defense motion for directed verdict at close of state's case denied by the court.
Court conducts a colloquy with the defendant as to his choice NOT to testify on his own behalf and finds the decision to be free and voluntary.  
Jury in the box 9:55 am. State and defense rest.  Testimony closed.  Court delivers instruction to the jury.  Court instructed jury.  Closing arguments by state and defense.  Alternate juror (#6) selected by lot and released.  Jury retired at the hour of 11:25 am to deliberate in the charge of Sheriff's Deputies Sanfillipo and Spottek who were duly sworn for that purpose.  
At the hour of 1:40 pm the jury returned and, by their foreperson(#13), brought in a verdict:
COUNT 1: We the jury find the defendant Guilty of repeated acts of sexual assault of a child.
Court polled and discharged the jury.  Verdict received and filed.  Court granted state's motion for judgment on the verdict and denied defense motion for judgment not withstanding the verdict. Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction. Court will order a PSI and remands the defendant pending sentencing on 03-06-2015 at 8:15 am.

 Jury panel in court.  Voir dire proceeded at the hour of  10:20 am.  
Thirteen (13) good and lawful citizens of the County of Milwaukee, WI qualified to serve as jurors in the above entitled cause were duly impanelled and sworn.  Jury list received and filed.   Court instructed jury.  Opening statements by state and defense. Court recessed for lunch. Jury out of box at 11:55 am and directed to return by 1:15pm.
All parties and defendant present in court at 1:20 pm. Trial proceeded.  Sworn for the state:  James W., T.B. (05-23-1998), T.B. (05-23-1998), Nakia S., Officer Louise Bray (MPD).
